'''John La Fave''' (born in [[Milwaukee]], July 13, 1949) is a [[Wisconsin]] [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] politician. He served as the [[State legislature (United States)|state representative]] for Wisconsin's 23rd [[Wisconsin State Assembly|Assembly]] District from 1993–2003, when he became the [[Register of Deeds]] for [[Milwaukee County, Wisconsin]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://county.milwaukee.gov/JohnLaFave7849.htm| title=John La Fave| work=[[Milwaukee County, Wisconsin]]}}</ref>
La Fave graduated from [[Wauwatosa West High School]] in 1967, and received a B.S. degree in education from the [[University of Wisconsin]] in 1971. He worked as a sales representative and an [[elementary school]] teacher before his 1992 election to the [[Wisconsin State Legislature|legislature]]. He is married.
La Fave has practiced [[Transcendental Meditation]] since the late 1960s, and attended a special mass-meditation event at the [[Maharishi University of Management]] in Iowa held in the wake of the [[9/11 attacks]].<ref>{{cite news| url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=ULQaAAAAIBAJ&pg=6659,2315287| title=Sit still, close your eyes, and think peace| first=Jim| last=Stingl| work=[[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]]| date=October 3, 2001| page=1B}}{{dead link|date=August 2017}}</ref>
